{"tid":1706159,"cid":19,"subCid":0,"title":"科大聽日繼續停課！","createTime":"2019-11-11T04:24:22.000Z","updateTime":"2019-11-11T04:47:58.000Z","uid":4238,"like":13,"dislike":0,"uniUserReply":10,"replies":[{"pid":"f9bcc9453e84fbf75204e977a316744e6335b650","tid":1706159,"uid":4238,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-11-11T04:24:22.000Z","msg":"Message from Provost and Vice-President for Administration and Business<br />\n=============================================<br />\n<br />\n<br />\nDear students, faculty and staff,<br />\n<br />\nIn view of the escalating tension and unrest in different parts of Hong Kong and the transport disruption, classes and official activities will be cancelled on Tuesday, November 12 2019. Staff except with special duties are not required to return to campus to work. Please check with your supervisors if you have any questions.<br />\n<br />\nAll University offices, Library and indoor sports facilities will be closed. Outdoor sports facilities including the tennis courts, seafront outdoor basketball court and the mini soccer pitch will remain open. As for the retail outlets and on-campus catering services, Campus Services Office (CSO) will keep you posted on their opening hours via email.<br />\n<br />\nMany of our members have expressed concerns on the personal safety after the vandalism on campus last Friday, which may involve non-HKUST members. In order to enhance tighter security and allay the safety concerns, the University will implement access control in all the entrance gates on campus immediately. Only HKUST members and authorised persons are allowed to enter the campus. Members of the HKUST community are required to bring your relevant identity card for checking before entering campus. We will also deploy more security measures in different parts on campus including staff quarters and student hostels.<br />\n<br />\nWe will continue to monitor and assess situation daily; and issue updates in due course.<br />\n<br />\nAll of us are advised to adopt a safety first approach.<br />\n<br />\nSincerely,<br />\n<br />\nLionel NI, Provost<br />\nMark HODGSON, Vice-President for Administration and Business"},{"pid":"6be4b1fbf1b1acade0f04091abeb50ea16444dcc","tid":1706159,"uid":211651,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-11-11T04:26:33.000Z","msg":"史維 condemn 呀"},{"pid":"518298e67c49228b429c2570cdfd2681df653a88","tid":1706159,"uid":124722,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-11-11T04:26:35.000Z","msg":"一大<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/agree.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"6e645bfe1e3ddb638d4220389feaccfef68989fd","tid":1706159,"uid":200973,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2019-11-11T04:26:50.000Z","msg":"仲有進出管制<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/smile.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"9188c6d508ecc25de396506f167271e8fbe2fcc7","tid":1706159,"uid":211651,"like":2,"dislike":1,"score":1,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-11-11T04:27:11.000Z","msg":"又匿埋係email 後面，仲要唔敢自己send"},{"pid":"b91c9dc606fece42136522379ff69eac1ff316b8","tid":1706159,"uid":161190,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2019-11-11T04:27:35.000Z","msg":"咁多科大生<img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/heard.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"https://na.cx/i/ZHRQMSa.png\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fna.cx%2Fi%2FZHRQMSa.png&h=6f3b78f7&s={SIZE}\" />"},{"pid":"24f438c080d23c550bc0e4314345a2bc3e79085f","tid":1706159,"uid":4238,"like":2,"dislike":0,"score":2,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-11-11T04:27:53.000Z","msg":"<span style=\"color: red;\"><span style=\"font-size: xx-large;\">繼李慧琼同謝振中後嘅科大傑山校友<img src=\"/assets/faces/big/dead.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/big/dead.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/big/dead.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /></span></span><br />\n<img src=\"https://na.cx/i/f7DfXYO.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fna.cx%2Fi%2Ff7DfXYO